topic.title: Synthetic EP Command

note.p: Remove in RevBThis feature is only available in the revision B switch

body.p: The Synthetic EP Command is used to set and get the status of Synthetic EP.

The sub command codes:
0x0 - Synthetic EP Polling
0x1 - Synthetic EP Remove
0x2 - Synthetic EP Insert

row.entry: Logical Port is not Capable for Insert

entry.p: Logical Port already has Synthetic EP

topic.title: Synthetic EP — Polling Sub-Command

section.p: The Synthetic EP Polling sub-command is used to get the status of Synthetic EP, which includes the following information:
1. Class Code of the Synthetic EP CSR
2. Vendor ID & Device ID of the Synthetic EP CSR
3. Command Register of the Synthetic EP CSR
4. Bar Register of the Synthetic EP CSR
Note: For logical port which do not have Synthetic EP instance inserted, all the status will be set to zero.

topic.title: Synthetic EP — Insert Sub-Command

section.p: The Synthetic EP Insert sub-command is used to re-insert the Synthetic EP to the DSP. The Synthetic EP can only be inserted under the following conditions:
1. DSP has a valid Synthetic EP instance
2. Synthetic EP is in DSPEPSIM_NONE state
3. DSP is capable of hot-plug and attention button is not defined
4. If DSP is bound, the physical port is in Dl_Down state
